<div id="home" class="scroll-top">

<p>My group works on machine learning for natural language processing and knowledge representation. I completed my PhD in 2020 from the Language Technologies Institute at Carnegie Mellon University. My thesis advisers were <a class="no-underline" href="http://www.cs.cmu.edu/~wcohen/">William Cohen</a> and <a class="no-underline" href="http://www.cs.cmu.edu/~rsalakhu/">Russ Salakhutdinov</a>. Before that I did Electrical Engineering at <a class="no-underline" href="http://www.iitk.ac.in/">IIT Kanpur</a>, where I worked with <a class="no-underline" href="http://www.cse.iitk.ac.in/users/amit/">Amitabha Mukerjee</a>. In between I worked at <a class="no-underline" href="https://www.qualcomm.com/invention/research">Qualcomm Research</a> in San Diego, USA.<br>
</p>
<p>
Current topics of interest include:
<ul>
	<li> Question answering and information retrieval </li>
	<li> Reasoning over structured and unstructured knowledge </li>
	<li> Robustness to corrupted text inputs </li>
	<li> Misinformation / propaganda detection </li>
	<li> Model calibration for inherently subjective NLP tasks </li>
</ul>
</p>
